Full Description: Kiiosk.com is the simplest, easiest and most fun way to read the news!  There are lots of News Readers out there, but the trouble is you have to go out and find all the news you want to import.  In the Kiiosk, we've pulled news from thousands of sources and serve it up by category and topic, leaving you with great news and no wasted time trying to find it! What's more? Members (signup is FREE, of course) can comment, vote, save, share and interact with the news, and with eachother!  We've made the social layers of Kiiosk easy as pie, with just a click you'll be saving, sharing and voting your favorite news stories to the top of the popularity list!   We've also created a customizable platform for our members to customize their interface, define their own news topics and even sign up to get distributions of news ("NewsDrops") automatically delivered to their inbox at intervals and times that they choose.  We've made getting the news so easy, you'll never have to leave your desk!  We've also added nifty features like News by Email requests.  You can simply send an email to newsdrop@kiiosk.com, leaving the subject blank, or populating the subject line with a topic of interest, and we'll get right back to you with the news on that topic! Last but not least, we've made Kiiosk completely extensible.  Not ready to give up your current news reader? That's ok! You can use our RSS feeds and get high quality Kiiosk news right in your current reader! (and you won't even hurt our feelings!).

Full Description: EMPIRE Translations is a full-range multilingual translation agency providing language services internationally to individuals, businesses, institutions and non-profit organizations. We build a multifaceted approach to each client’s unique needs thanks to our agility, innovative ideas, and teamwork. Our company is a one-stop solution for any organization seeking superior translations at highly competitive rates. Why Choose Empire Translations     At EMPIRE Translations, we provide the best 100% human services.     We take the time to listen to our clients and understand their business needs to deliver best results that will surpass their expectations.     We are committed to providing personable, reliable, and quality service at a competitive price in every job we undertake.     Our company draws from a world-class team of experienced and talented language professionals, including thousands of translators, industry-specific engineers, editors, proofreaders, top-notch project managers, IT, testing, and other specialists.     Only native speakers of the target language with the degrees in their respective fields are deployed for every project.     A dedicated manager is allocated for your project who solely looks after your translation process making your experience easy and pleasant.     EMPIRE Translations employs industry-leading CAT tools to improve efficiency and lower costs for our clients. We utilize translation memory (TM), which leverages previous translations to improve accuracy and consistency on new translation projects. In addition, we employ terminology management and glossary tools to build and manage client-specific glossaries—including abbreviations and branded terms for products/services. We welcome all kinds of projects, whether it is a simple, one-time project or a complex, on-going one.  We also handle overnight and rush translation jobs to help you meet challenging turnaround requirements.

Letterpress work is crisper than offset work because of its impression into the paper, giving greater visual definition to the type and artwork. Their journey began on first date back in 2010 when Mike and Shaun discovered that they both shared a love for letterpress printing. A long and excited conversation on the history of graphic design and relief printing was followed shortly by cohabitation. A year later they bought their first press, an Adana 8×5. This year, after years of saving and searching, they secured a 1949 Vandercook 3 proofing press for larger pieces.
